          "criteria": "confirmed or suspected rupture",
          "treatment": "Immediate laparotomy. Category-1 C-section. Deliver fetus within 5 minutes if alive. Repair uterine defect (debride edges, closure in layers). Hysterectomy if repair impossible (extensive damage, atonic bleeding, placenta accreta). Massive transfusion. IV broad-spectrum antibiotics. ICU admission. Monitor for DIC, AKI."
